    <para>
Pressing <keycap>Q</keycap> on most screens
exits &app;.
&app; tries to gracefully log out and shut down all server connections.
If &app; cannot log out of a remote server because the remote server is
down, press <keycap>CTRL</keycap>-<keycap>C</keycap>
(after <keycap>Q</keycap> to terminate &app;).</para>

    <para>
Use <keycap>CTRL</keycap>-<keycap>Z</keycap> to temporarily suspend &app;
and drop back to the shell prompt.
&app; remains suspended in the background, and may be restarted by using
the shell's <command>fg</command> command.</para>

    <note>
      <para>
Connections to remote mail servers may be disconnected
for inactivity if &app; remains suspended for a prolonged period of time.
When suspended, &app; cannot maintain any active connections to remote
mail servers.</para>
    </note>
